<h1><span id=3D"hs_cos_wrapper_name" class=3D"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper=
_meta_field hs_cos_wrapper_type_text" style=3D"" data-hs-cos-general-type=
=3D"meta_field" data-hs-cos-type=3D"text">Lumens to Watts Conversion Chart =
(from 100 to 10000 Lumens)</span></h1>
</div>
<article>
<span id=3D"hs_cos_wrapper_post_body" class=3D"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrappe=
r_meta_field hs_cos_wrapper_type_rich_text" style=3D"" data-hs-cos-general-=
type=3D"meta_field" data-hs-cos-type=3D"rich_text"><p class=3D"text-body fo=
nt-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb-[2px]"><span>Our lumens=
 to watts conversion chart below simplifies the correlation between these t=
wo light measurements, ranging from 100 to 10,000 lumens.</span></p>
<!--more-->
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><span>Armed with this knowledge, as business owners and homeowners,=
 you'll be able to compare and contrast the main types of lighting in terms=
 of watts and lumens.</span></p>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><span>Whether you're looking to upgrade your commercial lighting or=
 are simply curious about how much energy your current lighting setup consu=
mes, this conversion chart has all you need.</span></p>
<h2 class=3D"font-bold text-gray-800 text-h3 leading-[36px] pt-[21px] pb-[2=
px] [&amp;_a]:underline-offset-[6px] [&amp;_.underline]:underline-offset-[6=
px]" style=3D"font-weight: normal;">Lumens to watts conversion chart</h2>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><span>Without further ado, let's dive into the lumens comparison ta=
ble below.</span></p>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><span>This user-friendly chart serves as a practical tool to compar=
e lumens to watts and vice versa, thus <strong>simplifying the process of m=
aking lighting choices.</strong></span></p>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><span>It is particularly useful for understanding watts to lumens c=
onversion for the most popular types of bulbs.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><span>With this at your fingertips, you will be better equipped to =
select the best lighting solutions, enhancing efficiency while reducing cos=
ts.</span></p>
<blockquote>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]" style=3D"font-weight: normal;">You'll see that switching to LED lig=
hts isn't just a bright idea=E2=80=94it's a smart one!</p>
</blockquote>
<p><em>Note: The figures in the chart below are all approximate wattage</em=
></p>
<div dir=3D"ltr" align=3D"left">
<table style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; table-layout: fixed; margin-left=
: auto; margin-right: auto; width: 96.463%; border: 1px solid #99acc2; heig=
ht: 1534.5px;"><colgroup><col style=3D"width: 17.3623%;" width=3D"76"><col =
style=3D"width: 16.3606%;" width=3D"95"><col style=3D"width: 21.0334%;" wid=
th=3D"131"><col style=3D"width: 13.6912%;" width=3D"107"><col style=3D"widt=
h: 14.0234%;" width=3D"95"><col style=3D"width: 17.1953%;" width=3D"119"></=
colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style=3D"height: 79.5px;">
<td style=3D"height: 79.5px; text-align: center;">
<p><strong>Lumens</strong></p>
</td>
<td style=3D"height: 79.5px; text-align: center;">
<p><strong>LED&nbsp;</strong></p>
</td>
<td style=3D"height: 79.5px; text-align: center;">
<p><strong>Incandescent&nbsp;</strong></p>
</td>
<td style=3D"height: 79.5px; text-align: center;">
<p><strong>Halogen&nbsp;</strong></p>
</td>
<td style=3D"height: 79.5px; text-align: center;">
<p><strong>CFL&nbsp;</strong></p>
</td>
<td style=3D"height: 79.5px; text-align: center;">
<p><strong>Metal Halide</strong></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style=3D"height: 52.5px;">
<td style=3D"height: 52.5px; text-align: center;">
<p><span>100</span></p>
</td>
<td style=3D"height: 52.5px; text-align: center;">
<p><span>1-2</span></p>
</td>
<td style=3D"height: 52.5px; text-align: center;">
<p><span>15</span></p>
</td>
<td style=3D"height: 52.5px; text-align: center;">
<p><span>10</span></p>
</td>
<td style=3D"height: 52.5px; text-align: center;">
<p><span>3-4</span></p>
</td>
<td style=3D"height: 52.5px; text-align: center;">
<p><span>10-15</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style=3D"height: 52.5px;">
