<li class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] my-[5px] [=
&amp;&gt;ol]:!pt-0 [&amp;&gt;ol]:!pb-0 [&amp;&gt;ul]:!pt-0 [&amp;&gt;ul]:!p=
b-0" value=3D"4"><strong><strong class=3D"font-bold">Incandescent:</strong>=
</strong><span> Lumens =3D Watts x 15</span></li>
<li class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] my-[5px] [=
&amp;&gt;ol]:!pt-0 [&amp;&gt;ol]:!pb-0 [&amp;&gt;ul]:!pt-0 [&amp;&gt;ul]:!p=
b-0" value=3D"5"><strong><strong class=3D"font-bold">Metal Halide</strong><=
/strong><span>: Lumens =3D Watts x 60</span></li>
</ul>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><span>Note that these equations reflect the <em>average</em> lumens=
 produced per watt for each bulb type.</span></p>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><span>The <em>actual</em> values may vary slightly depending on the=
 specific bulb. For an accurate measurement, it's always best to check the =
packaging or the manufacturer's specifications.</span></p>
<blockquote>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><strong>Note that, for the examples below, we're using LED conversi=
on rates.</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<h3 class=3D"font-bold text-gray-800 text-h4 leading-[30px] pt-[15px] pb-[2=
px] [&amp;_a]:underline-offset-[6px] [&amp;_.underline]:underline-offset-[6=
px]" style=3D"font-weight: normal;"><span class=3D"font-bold">Example watt =
to lumen conversion</span></h3>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><span>So, how many lumens is 1,000 watts? How do you compute for LE=
D watts to lumens? We can apply the formula above for a 1,000 watts to lume=
ns calculation.</span></p>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><span>This means <strong>1000 watts x 80 lumens =3D 80,000 lumens.<=
/strong> This shows that a 1,000-watt LED bulb would give off around 80,000=
 lumens.</span></p>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><span>By comparison, a traditional incandescent bulb would only pro=
duce around 15,000 lumens while consuming the same amount of power.</span><=
/p>
<h3 class=3D"font-bold text-gray-800 text-h4 leading-[30px] pt-[15px] pb-[2=
px] [&amp;_a]:underline-offset-[6px] [&amp;_.underline]:underline-offset-[6=
px]" style=3D"font-weight: normal;"><span class=3D"font-bold">Example lumen=
 to watt conversion</span></h3>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><span>To illustrate the reverse conversion process, let's consider =
how many watts is 800 lumens? To make this conversion, we'll follow the for=
mula given above, but in a reverse manner.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><span>Firstly, remember that in the case of LED lights, Lumens =3D =
Watts x 80. Therefore, if we rearrange the equation, we find that </span><s=
trong><strong class=3D"font-bold">Watts =3D Lumens / 80</strong></strong><s=
pan>.</span></p>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><span>So, for 800 lumens, the calculation would be <strong>800 lume=
ns / 80 =3D 10 watts.</strong> The result shows that an LED bulb providing =
800 lumens only consumes about 10 watts of power.</span></p>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><span>By contrast, a traditional incandescent bulb would require ap=
proximately 53 watts to become as luminous as a comparable LED bulb.</span>=
</p>
<blockquote>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><strong>This stark difference underscores the superior energy effic=
iency of LED lights. By opting for LEDs, you can enjoy considerable energy =
savings, which in turn translates into significant cost reductions on your =
electricity bills.</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<h4 class=3D"font-bold text-gray-800 text-h3 leading-[36px] pt-[21px] pb-[2=
px] [&amp;_a]:underline-offset-[6px] [&amp;_.underline]:underline-offset-[6=
px]" style=3D"font-weight: normal;"><span class=3D"font-bold">Ready to make=
 the switch to LED lights?</span></h4>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><span>If you've made it this far, you're likely serious about makin=
g a significant upgrade to your lighting solutions. You've come to understa=
nd the high efficiency of LED lights and how they can reduce your energy co=
nsumption and electricity bills, especially when you consider the <a href=
=3D"https://blog.feslighting.com/pros-and-cons-of-led-lights-for-business" =
rel=3D"noopener" target=3D"_blank">pros and cons of LED lights</a>.</span><=
/p>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><span>But, where do you start?&nbsp;</span></p>
<blockquote>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><span><strong>We're here to help! FES Lighting offers a wide range =
of high-quality, energy-efficient LED lighting solutions tailored to your n=
eeds.</strong></span></p>
</blockquote>
<p class=3D"text-body font-regular text-gray-800 leading-[24px] pt-[9px] pb=
-[2px]"><span><span style=3D"font-weight: bold;">Call us today</span> to le=
arn more about how we can help your business save energy and money while br=
ightening up your space! Make the smart move today and take your first step=
 towards a brighter, more energy-efficient future.</span></p>
